Manchester United and Arsenal dedicated Sunday's game to the support of LGBT charity Stonewall's Rainbow Laces campaign, which the club is involved in alongside our principal partner Aon, a global leader in promoting diversity and inclusion. 

Team captains Michael Carrick and Laurent Koscielny showed a sign of public support, viewed by millions of fans across the globe, when they exchanged giant rainbow laces before kick-off. The laces are symbolic of Stonewall's inclusion work in football and other sports in recent years.

The Reds have also signed up to take part in a Manchester United Legends XI match against a Stonewall team, to commemorate the charity's 25th anniversary.
